15/05/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- The army announced on Saturday (May 14th) that security forces have killed at least 12 Kurdish rebels spotted crossing the border from Iraq. 
This happened on Friday and early Saturday in operations in the southeast province of Sirnak. 
The army also announced one soldier died in a mine blast in the province of Hakkari. 
(Anadolu news agency, Press TV, Xinhua, Vatan - 14/05/11)
